        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): add pagination support for drive list and info",
        "body": "Closes #93928\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFeishu drive list and info lacked pagination. When a folder had more than the default page size (10 items), list returned only the first page and info returned `File not found` for items on subsequent pages.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdded `page_size`, `page_token`, and `all` parameters to the drive schema. `listFolder` loops through pages with `MAX_LIST_PAGES = 100` guard. `getFileInfo` searches across all pages before concluding the file is missing.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx -e 'import { FeishuDriveSchema } from \"./extensions/feishu/src/drive-schema.ts\"; ...'\n\nFeishu drive schema: Type.Union with 9 actions\n\n  action: list\n    page_size:  true   (optional, default 10, max 100)\n    page_token: true   (optional, from previous response)\n    all:        true   (optional, auto-fetch all pages)\n\n  action: info\n    page_size:  false  (info by file_token, no pagination needed)\n    ...\n\n  action: list_comments\n    page_size:  true\n    page_token: true\n\n  action: list_comment_replies\n    page_size:  true\n    page_token: true\n\nMAX_LIST_PAGES = 100 (prevents infinite pagination loops)\n```\n\nThe `listFolder` pagination loop follows the standard `has_more + next_page_token` pattern with a `MAX_LIST_PAGES = 100` hard stop. End-to-end test requires a real Feishu tenant.",
